# User-Facing Copy Review

**The maintainer owns all user-facing English copy.** Agents must not invent, polish, or commit wording without explicit approval.

This applies to UI, Discord bot replies, slash-command descriptions, email, error/empty-state text, onboarding, and help guides — anything a player or officer reads.

## Hard stops (never do these without maintainer approval)

- **Do not write or edit `messages/en-US.*`** — not even “small” typo fixes, hint tweaks, or keys added alongside a feature.
- **Do not write or edit `messages/pt-BR.*`** — translations come **after** English is approved, never in the same turn as drafting English.
- **Do not run `npm run i18n:translate`**, Google Translate, or any automated translation pipeline.
- **Do not edit English or localized strings in `scripts/discord/register-commands.mjs`** until the maintainer approves the English wording.
- **Do not embed new user-facing strings inline in TS/TSX** when the project uses i18n keys — draft the key + English value for review first.

If a feature needs copy, **stop implementation at the i18n boundary** and ask the maintainer to approve English before touching locale files.

## Required flow

1. **Draft only** — list affected message keys (or UI locations) and propose English text in chat. Use placeholders in code (`TODO: copy pending maintainer`) only if the maintainer agrees to land structure first.
2. **Wait** — do not proceed until the maintainer replies with approval, edited wording, or an explicit “use this exact text: …”.
3. **Apply English** — update `messages/en-US.*` (and inline strings if any) to match **exactly** what the maintainer approved.
4. **Translate** — update `messages/pt-BR.*` and Discord `description_localizations` from the **approved English only**. Hand-translate; do not auto-translate.
5. **Validate** — run `npm run i18n:validate` after locale edits.

## What counts as approval

| Counts | Does **not** count |
| --- | --- |
| Maintainer pastes exact strings in chat | Agent-drafted copy the maintainer has not seen |
| “Use that wording” / “approved” / “ship it” on a listed draft | Assumed approval because the task mentions a feature |
| Maintainer edits `en-US.json` themselves — treat their file as source of truth | Prior PR copy, training-data phrasing, or “sounds better” agent rewrites |
| Maintainer says “propagate my English changes to pt-BR” | Agent updating English and pt-BR in one step without review |

When the maintainer edits English locally, **read their committed or saved `en-US.json` as canonical** — do not revert or “improve” it; only propagate to pt-BR and Discord localizations.

## Agent checklist before any PR with copy

- [ ] Every new/changed `en-US` string was shown to the maintainer or copied from their edits
- [ ] `pt-BR` updated only from approved English (same PR is OK if maintainer asked for propagation)
- [ ] No automated translation used
- [ ] `npm run i18n:validate` passes

